# Project Structure & Conventions

## Stack

- **React 19** + **React Router v7** (framework mode, SPA — `ssr: false`)
- **TypeScript 5.9** (`strict`, `verbatimModuleSyntax`)
- **Tailwind CSS v4**
- **Vite 8**
- **TanStack Query** for server state
- **Ky** for HTTP (via `HttpClient` abstraction — never call `fetch` directly for PokeAPI)
- **Playwright** for E2E tests
- **Oxfmt** for formatting, **Oxlint** for linting (Oxc toolchain)

## Folder Layout

```
app/
  routes/          # One file per route segment
  components/      # Shared UI components (no route logic)
  hooks/           # Custom React hooks (TanStack Query wrappers)
  lib/             # Pure utilities and helpers (no React)
    http/          # HttpClient abstraction + Ky implementation
    pokemon/       # PokeAPI client, mappers, query keys, utils
  types/           # Shared TypeScript types / interfaces
  root.tsx         # Root layout + global ErrorBoundary
  routes.ts        # Route manifest
  app.css          # Global styles (Tailwind entry)
public/            # Static assets (favicon, images)
tests/             # Playwright E2E specs
```

- Co-locate component-specific files (styles, tests, sub-components) next to the component.
- Prefix server-only modules with `.server.ts` and client-only with `.client.ts`.
- Use the `~/` path alias (maps to `app/`) for all internal imports.

## React Router v7

- Always use the generated typed `Route` object from `./+types/<route>` — never cast manually.
- Export `loader` / `action` from route files; keep business logic in `lib/`.
- Every route should export an `ErrorBoundary`; use `isRouteErrorResponse` to distinguish HTTP errors.
- Prefer `meta` exports over `<title>` tags inside components.
- Use `<Link>` / `<NavLink>` instead of `<a>` for in-app navigation.
- Use `useFetcher` for background mutations; avoid redundant `useEffect` + `fetch` patterns.

```tsx
// ✅ typed loader + component
import type { Route } from "./+types/pokemon";

export async function loader({ params }: Route.LoaderArgs) {
  return fetchPokemon(params.id);
}

export default function Pokemon({ loaderData }: Route.ComponentProps) {
  return <div>{loaderData.name}</div>;
}
```

## React

- Functional components only — no class components.
- Keep components small and single-purpose; extract logic into custom hooks.
- Never call hooks conditionally or inside loops.
- Derive values from existing state instead of mirroring them with `useEffect`.
- Use `useCallback` / `useMemo` only when profiling shows it matters.

```tsx
// ❌ mirroring state
const [fullName, setFullName] = useState("");
useEffect(() => setFullName(`${first} ${last}`), [first, last]);

// ✅ derived value
const fullName = `${first} ${last}`;
```

## Data Fetching

- PokeAPI access goes through `PokeApiClient` (injected via `PokeApiClientContext`).
- Query keys live in `app/lib/pokemon/pokemonQueryKeys.ts`.
- Route components consume data via hooks in `app/hooks/` (`useRegions`, `usePokedex`, etc.).
- Validate external API responses at the boundary before mapping to view models.

## Accessibility

- Prefer native semantic elements over ARIA roles (`<dialog>`, `<meter>`, `<output>`).
- Loading indicators use `<output aria-live="polite">` (see `Spinner`).
- Modals use `<dialog open>` with a backdrop `<button>` for dismiss — do not put `onClick` on static `div`s.
- Backdrop dismiss button uses `aria-label="Dismiss dialog"`; the close icon button uses `"Close dialog"`.
- Do not disable jsx-a11y rules — fix the markup instead.

## TypeScript

- `strict: true` is enforced — no suppressions without a documented reason.
- Use `type` for shapes and unions; use `interface` only when extending.
- Use `verbatimModuleSyntax`: always use `import type` for type-only imports.
- Never use `any`; prefer `unknown` with a type guard when the shape is truly unknown.
- Validate external data at the boundary (API responses, URL params) before typing.

```ts
// ✅ type-only import
import type { Pokemon } from "~/types/pokemon";

// ✅ unknown → typed at boundary
function parsePokemon(raw: unknown): Pokemon {
  // validate shape here
}
```

## Code Quality

Single config file per tool — no overrides that disable rules.

| Tool | Config | Scripts |
|---|---|---|
| Oxfmt | `.oxfmtrc.json` | `npm run fmt`, `npm run fmt:check` |
| Oxlint | `.oxlintrc.json` | `npm run lint`, `npm run lint:fix` |

Oxlint defaults:
- Plugins: `typescript`, `unicorn`, `oxc`, `react`, `jsx-a11y`, `import`
- Category `correctness` at `error`
- `options.denyWarnings: true` — warnings fail CI
- React settings include `Link` / `NavLink` from React Router

Oxfmt defaults:
- Tailwind class sorting via `sortTailwindcss.stylesheet` → `./app/app.css`
- Shared `ignorePatterns` with Oxlint (`build/`, `.react-router/`, `node_modules/`, `test-results/`)

Run before committing:

```bash
npm run fmt:check && npm run lint && npm run typecheck && npm run test
```

## Testing

- E2E tests live in `tests/` and run against the real PokeAPI via `npm run dev`.
- Playwright config: `playwright.config.ts` (base URL `http://localhost:5173`).
- Prefer `getByRole` and `data-testid` selectors; keep the suite small and stable.
- CI runs E2E in a separate job with Chromium only.

## General

- Keep functions small and single-purpose; shallow control flow over nesting.
- All code and comments must be in **English**.
- Comments explain **why**, not what.
- Fail fast: validate inputs at the top of a function; avoid deeply nested error handling.
